# Performance Standards

## Service Worker (Background)
- Keep startup time < 500ms — lazy-load heavy modules
- Use `chrome.alarms` instead of `setInterval` for periodic tasks
- Avoid persistent connections — service workers hibernate after 30s idle
- Cache API responses in `chrome.storage.local` with TTL

## Content Scripts
- DOM queries must be scoped: `element.querySelector()` not `document.querySelector()` where possible
- Batch DOM reads before DOM writes (avoid layout thrashing)
- Use `MutationObserver` for dynamic content, not polling
- Disconnect observers when no longer needed

## React Side Panel
- Use `React.memo()` for components receiving stable props
- Use `useMemo`/`useCallback` for expensive computations and stable references
- Implement virtualization for lists > 50 items
- Images: use `loading="lazy"` and WebP format

## Bundle Size
- Target: < 2MB total extension size, < 500KB per entrypoint chunk
- Tree-shake unused imports — no barrel imports from large libraries
- Dynamic import heavy dependencies: `const x = await import('./heavy')`

## Metrics
- Side Panel Time to Interactive: < 1s
- Content Script injection: < 100ms
- Background script cold start: < 500ms
